@node Installation "Connectix Cam as Webcam ON Amiga V1.0 - Installation"
@prev Where
@next ToDo
@help HelpPage
@font XEN.font 11

@{b}Installation:@{ub}
Please Get the Following Files from aminet

Sgrab.lha
FTPMount_1_0.lha
FTPMount_upd.lha
jpeglibrary40.lha

Then install them to your Harddrive Preferable to a Directory
that is easy to get to Like inside your Internet Dir 
When you install Ftpmount first open up a Dir tool
Opus or Disk master then Copy the Update file to the main Ftpmount
archive now use the Install Icon and have Ftpmount Load on bootup
This will help Prevent Crashes . For me my system Crashes everythime
I load Ftpmount after I have Loaded a few Prgs . I found that it wont
crash my system if it is loaded First.

Next install Sgrab Place it in the Webcam Dir and/or in C.

Now copy the Arexx scripts to Rexx (this is assigned on startup
Usually your S dir )

If you have Different settings or Other Places on your system you
want these files Just go into the Fastcam and Slowcam text files
and alter the info .

There are Two Different Camera Scripts
Fastcam and Slowcam

Fastcam is for faster machines (it also is good to see if your
is actually sending the files over To the Ftpsite)

Slowcam Is for slower machines It works great with 030 @25 
or Higher 

The defaults are Dh0:internet/webcam/ for the cam
and dh0:rexxc/ for the arexx scripts

Set your Ftpmount drawer for your Ftp site on your server
this is easy all you need is the Ftp site info and a little time.
icon inside The Hosts Directory for Ftpmount find an the localhost
Icon Rename it to webcam (or a name you want) then use the pulldown
menu to get info on the icon now set your Ftp site paramiters 
inside the ICOn.
then hit save.

The arexx script is set to Jpeg and is at Image Quality of 50%
you can change that By opening a text reader like Ed or Ced 
and edit it that way . 

After you have configured everything In the Scripts you can now
hit the Icon and it will run your cam .

