@node Errors "Errors and what to do  - Errors"
@prev Index
@help HelpPage
@font XEN.font 11

@{b}What to do for errors :@{ub}
if anything Fails then Check to make sue you have configured
everything Correctly  

If the script runs fine and it gives errors (expecially on 
grabtimer.rexx.5) after loging into your Ftp server keep an Eye
on it because this is the first time you have started sending info
to your site or you crashed on save last time you were using the 
cam . This configuration is Stable It works fine on my
Amiga 600 030 @33 mzh Machine

Errors
Screen 
this means you didnt set the screen to be grabed right Or altered
the script By accident
Solution
Look at Fastcam or Slow cam to see what screen you are grabing make sure
it says Quickcam
Enviroment Not found
This means that Ftpmount or Sgrab isnt available
Make sure you have assigned the correct Directories to them
This also will apply to The camera also so make sure you have it all
set up correct.

 @{"Read On" link FaQ}

@endnode
@node FAQ "Frequently Asked Questions  - FAQ"
@prev Errors
@help HelpPage
@font XEN.font 11

@{b}Q.:@{ub} The top of the cam pic why does it have all of the settings from 
   the cam pic .

@{b}A.:@{ub} This is due to No real Arexx port on the cam software so we cant
   really get a clean pic without that there

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Sometimes after running the cam for a few minutes I get an error

@{b}A.:@{ub} This is due to something Doing a task while the cam soft is trying
   to Accomplish its goals this should not Happen on Faster systems
   It will occure from time to time on slow systems Like mine.

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Can I have the Image grabed longer than 1 minute

@{b}A.:@{ub} this isnt Recomended Due to Ftpmount not liking to stay online 
   longer than a minute I am going to look into a way to keep it online
   longer Hopefully up to 30 mins for those who want to Have That long
   of a delay in their cam Pics

@{b}Q.:@{ub} How do I shut the cam off without Shutting off the Computer

@{b}A.:@{ub} This is easy . First you freeze the cam on the image you want to 
   be the last Image . Then wait 
   when the screen snaps(flashes) make sure with Webtv or a browser
   that it did send . and when you are Happy with the Results Click on 
   Sgrabs window this will allow you to Then use the Pull down menu's
   select Quit then wait for the Cli to show an error which should close 
   the cli Window then you can shut off the cam soft and continue as if you 
   didnt have it on at all.

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Can I use the cam in the Dark

@{b}A.:@{ub} No. Well actually all cameras need a Light source if it is totally Dark
   forget it but since you will be at least having the Monitor on you wont
   be completely in the dark. Just play with the Exposure and contrast till
   you get the Results (higher the Exposure the slower the cam but the 
   brighter the image)

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Can I take my cam outside

@{b}A.:@{ub} Yes connectix sells a 12 foot extention for the cam  just hit their site
   and check it out . But remember to use a Filter or Sunglass lense .
   It can be Quite Bright outside.

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Can I have a Camera tripod instead of this tiny Triangle with my cam

@{b}A.:@{ub} Gee This is easy to answer. The cam comes Threaded for a standard tripod
   mount Connectix sells a Small tripod They sell it cheaper than My
   local walmart (suprizing isnt it) .

@{b}Q.:@{ub} Can I use a color cam with this 

@{b}A.:@{ub} Yes . But it has to be the Acqvid as the Quickcam Pak dosent do color
   I have not seen the Acqvid in Action with a color camera yet but have
   been assured that it does work.

